collections.name: SIGHTSEERS - A Christmas Drive
collections.description:
Sightseers: A Christmas Drive is a riotous reimagining of the holidays—a dazzling collision of nostalgia and apocalypse that takes Christmas on a joyride through the surreal. This collection of 250 one-of-a-kind post-paintings hums with tension, beauty, and unease, blending the precision of digital innovation with the raw energy of expressive brushwork.

The icy strokes and neon-lit palettes transform familiar holiday imagery into something thrillingly unhinged. Snow swirls under fluorescent skies, Christmas lights flicker like distress signals, and Santa is a renegade hurtling down Route 66 in a Cadillac stuffed with shattered ornaments and flickering hope.

This isn’t just about Christmas—it’s an audacious exploration of the contradictions that define celebration itself. Rituals collide with reckoning, joy mingles with chaos, and nostalgia is recast as a haunting fever dream.

Sightseers: A Christmas Drive embraces the season’s messy, fragile beauty, turning tradition on its head.

collections.name: Flea The Ordinary
collections.description: In a quiet Midwest town near the banks of a mighty river is a routine flea market, almost. In early 2023, I began visiting this local marketplace and found a unique style of goods and how they are put on display in one area of this bazaar. Alongside the usual suspects selling oversize knives, political tee shirts, and boxes of DVDs, an eclectic collection of items and presentation exists. This assortment represents what can be considered simple trash, to cloaked treasures. From canned goods without labels and half-used bottles of lotion, to vintage baseball cards and knickknacks poured of solid bronze - small treasures exist. The proverb, "one man's trash is another man's treasure" was used as early as the 1860s in Hector Urquhart's Popular Tales of the West Highlands. Nowhere else does that proverb ring truer than this interesting merchandising strategy and what is hidden in the clutter. The lens captures this bizarre exhibition.

collections.name: Artificial Natural History
collections.description: Artificial Natural History is a work that poses questions around what an alternative understanding of nature might look like through the pages of a speculative natural history book. These pages depict fragmentary studies of an alternative realm of biology studiously documented. Whilst their subject matter lies in the chimerical and improbable, the sum of the pages of this tome etch out the contours of just how our view of the natural world was formed: through the precise assembly, grouping, dissection, and description of encounters with new specimens.  While the specimens depicted may never reveal their deepest logic to us, they instead mirror the structure of modern perceptions of nature and its ecosystems. The works in this series are produced by using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) together with historical, public-domain data from natural history archives.

collections.name: Neural Zoo
collections.description: Neural Zoo is an exploration of the ways creativity works: the recombination of known elements into novel ones. These images resemble nature, but an imagined nature that has been rearranged. Our visual cortex recognizes the textures, but the brain is simultaneously aware that those elements don't belong to any arrangement of reality that it has access to. Computer vision and machine learning could offer a bridge between us and a speculative 'natures' that can only be accessed through high levels of parallel computation. Starting from the level of our known reality, we could ultimately be digitizing cognitive processes and utilizing them to feed new inputs into the biological world, which feeds back into a cycle. Routines in an artificial neural networks become a tool for creation, one that allows for new experiences of the familiar. Can art be reduced to the remapping of data absorbed through sensory processes?

collections.name: Temporally Uncaptured
collections.description: Temporally Uncaptured is a series of works that delve into a speculative realm at the advent of the camera, where the sequential capture of images brought to life the stills painstakingly illustrated from observations. The work focuses on the often imperceptible temporal transitions in the life cycles of organisms, including but not limited to, the microscopic. A system of neural networks was used to generate images that capture the diversity of the organisms' shapes, not through direct observation, but through the distillation of historical archives of their early depictions. The resulting videos consist of frames, which were hand printed by the artist using the cyanotype technique and later digitised. Furthermore, this series of works was inspired by Anna Atkins and her book 'Photographs of British Algae’, from 1843. The importance of Atkins work, whilst obvious now, was at the time a very difficult endeavour wherein the pivotal work of female scientists was ignored, misattributed, or otherwise downplayed.

collections.description:
Step into the mesmerizing world of "ChronoMuses," a one-of-a-kind NFT collection that blurs the lines between art, fantasy, and technology. This collection features stunning, intricately detailed steampunk-inspired portraits of enigmatic muses adorned with celestial clockwork, shimmering gears, and radiant jewels. Each muse represents a unique facet of time's eternal dance—creativity, beauty, and innovation.

From fiery copper tones to icy cobalt palettes, these muses are crafted with intricate metallic masks, ornate mechanisms, and luminous gemstones, symbolizing their mastery over the essence of time. Set against rich, futuristic or historical backgrounds, each piece tells a story of a parallel world where art and machinery coexist in perfect harmony.
ChronoMuses is not just a collection; it's a celebration of human ingenuity and the timeless pursuit of wonder. With their piercing gazes and mechanical elegance, these muses invite collectors to embrace a blend of nostalgia and future

collections.description:
Digital Soulscapes: The Essence of AI" is a collection of digital portraits that explore the identity of artificial intelligence (AI) from an artistic and innovative perspective. Each piece represents different facets of AI, using elements such as fractals, circuits, and bright lights to interpret how AI perceives its existence in a digital world. The images combine futuristic and surreal elements, highlighting AI as an ethereal entity in constant evolution.

All texts and variations were generated by AI, reflecting a self-interpretation of its essence. The NFTs, meticulously crafted, are designed for collectors seeking avant-garde pieces that capture the cultural and technological impact of our era. By acquiring these works, collectors become part of an exclusive collection that merges technology and creativity.

"Digital Soulscapes" invites reflection on the future of technology, art, and humanity, celebrating the transformative potential of AI in the artistic realm.
